caption: Great pub for a pint. I like the bathroom art.

Bills bar, if I wasn't a Buffalo fan the place wouldn't be exceptional. Service was friendly and attentive and prices comparable to similar places in the area.

Loved the open back patio, and they filled my wine glass all the way to the top :).  Great happy hour prices, and overall a great dive bar.

Awesome Bills bar with even better staff and a nice outdoor area in the back. The wings were absolutely delicious as well as the chicken poppers and tater tots. The best buckets special topped off our great afternoon. Definitely worth a visit for football Sunday, well any day considering how good the food was.

Great neighborhood bar with lots of space upstairs and a delightful patio out back. Owners are super friendly and drink selection is very good. Also, if you are in the mood for a sweet treat they have amazing ice cream sandwiches from Little Robin Bakery!

Exiles has the friendliest staff of any establishment I've ever visited. 10/10. Would recommend.

I rarely get online and post about my experiences in bars, be them good or bad. But I was in D.C. visiting a friend roughly 3 weeks ago and came upon Exiles by accident. Donnagh and his crew were incredibly hospitable, and really, it's everything that I look for in a neighborhood pub. Throw a ton of cash at them once this social distancing business in done and over with. A great place.
Just fine. Good service

I come to Exiles for trivia on Tuesday nights. They have good happy hour deals with great food. I’m a huge fan of their burgers and sliders as well as their fries. I really enjoy their fry sauce. There’s a great atmosphere on trivia nights both upstairs and downstairs.
They had this awesome band, Moon Raiser, upstairs.

ROCK CHALK JAYHAWK. Great to find a KU bar in DC to watch the game.

Great service, great bar. Went for the first stop for a birthday party and Brian has worked with me a couple days in advance to quickly and easily to reserve a couple tables. Bartender was expecting us and cranked out 22 great drinks in short order. Nice guy. Other owner was there too and friendly. Too bad we had to leave for our other dinner plans! We will be back! Highly recommend.
Great local place and always good people and staff are the best. Ever in the U St hood..stop by and see them.
Great bar. Fun events upstairs with a nice patio out back.

Chicken and Dumplings (very similar to pirogis) were amazing.  I’m going back for sure!  I hear they have live music upstairs, but can’t find a listing.

Terrific bar.  Food is great.  We had a show upstairs and they didn't dedicate a bartender for the bar upstairs, so that's why I didn't rate it 5 stars.  Maybe you'll disagree and say that it IS 5 stars.  It's pretty much 5 stars as far as I'm concerned.
It's the 5th best bar on U Street!

The owner works the bar some of the days and we had the pleasure of meeting him! The chicken and dumplings were amazing and the perfect comfort food for our tipsy selves on a rainy Friday night. The chicken sandwich was a bit chewy but we ordered just a few minutes before the kitchen closed. It is their most popular dish so I'm willing to call this a fluke. The ambience of the place was nice but it's a pretty small place. Nice for a quick meal or drinks after a long day when you don't want to go home yet.
Great food 🤤
Great sports bar,  funny staff
Love the back patio here and that they allow dogs. I ordered some delicious mules, and the staff were so thrilled my dog was visiting. I only wish they had some vegan options other than fries.

Good beer. Good bartender. Nice location

Been swinging by Exiles for the past 2ish years to watch the Bills games on Sundays during the football season. Each time the bartender / owner has gone out of his way to say hi, shake my hand, ask me how I’ve been, and make me feel at-home. Top notch service, friendly staff with a sense of humor, good food and reasonably priced beers. All adds up to this place being just like my old haunts in Rochester, NY and the only spot I’ll stop to watch the Bills in DC.
The bartender messed up my tab, charged me for an extra drink and then insulted me when I didn’t tip for the one drink I ordered.
We didn’t eat. The drinks were cold and the bartender had a sense of humor and offered outstanding service. I don’t make it to DC often but I’ll return to this venue as often as I can.

Exiles is a haven on U St! Original touches from when it was Stetson's along with updates that keep the feel. Great Irish whiskey and beer selection. Cocktails are well balanced. We had the fried chicken sandwich, brussel sprouts, and brisket sliders. Everything had a solid flavor and it was some of the best brisket I've ever had. The brussel sprouts were delicious and we had to get more of the garlic aioli! The owner and bartender, Donagh, takes time to chat, learn your name - and your drink! - and the rest of the staff were friendly and helpful. Trivia on Tuesdays, comedy and dance parties some nights all upstairs. I only wish it wasn't so far from home, otherwise I'd be there all the time!

caption: Carl is a gem. I had a stressful day at work and his genuity as hospitality literally made my night. I am literally about to cry just thinking about it (tears of joy, of course)!

What a bar should be. The food (especially the wings) are delicious. Plenty of space to meet old and new friends. Beer selection is top notch and the service is friendly, funny and on top of it. I especially like the outdoor seating in the back, great place to chill, eat some food and enjoy company.

Very solid neighborhood bar. Try their smoked wings, absolutely amazing.

A very nice bar with friendly staff! Beers and food are great, I recommend everything in the grilled meat / burger area, it's really a treat. The outdoor patio is a real plus as you can enjoy a night outside without noise and just with friends. In addition, the bar can host really nicely large events up to 200 persons and provide food and drinks at a really nice price (wings are spicy delicious)! A definite must in the area ;)
Good bar and friendly staff. I ordered drinks and some chips, and meat. They meal tasted nice.

Trivia was run through with all deliberate speed and as soon as it was over they shooed us out... It felt like they were obligated to do the trivia and it couldn't be over soon enough. The food was ok, beer prices normal for DC.

Had the BBQ Brisket sandwich here and it was so delicious. Nice little outside space that apparently is dog friendly. Good selection of beers on tap. Also the side order of fries came with two different types of mayo which is always a plus. Didn't have to wait long for the food or drinks which as you may have guessed it, ANOTHER plus.

Staff is great. The food is amazing! And its the best pint of Guinness on U St!  Definitely check out the Beer Dinners at the end of the month. I've been to 4 and they were all fantastic!  One of my favorite bars in DC!

Don't overthink it: get the wings. They are crispy and smoky and excellent. For drinks, there is a nice selection of rotating craft beers on tap. They also have a $4 "mystery beer" special which is a bunch of random craft odds and ends the bartender randomly pulls out. You can get some great surprises on the cheap. Nice come-as-you-are place. Seems like an owner is always on premise and working the bar or the floor.

The owners & bartenders are amazing! The owners were some of my favorite bartenders at a pub in Clarendon and they opened their own place.  The vibe is great if you enjoy lively pubs!  Make sure to check out the the second floor. The second floor has live music on Friday nights and a DJ on Saturday nights (The stairs are right in front of you as you enter the door but, somehow, easy to miss).  Also, the back patio is really nice! So check that out too if it's a nice night out.  Bonus: Your phone battery will never go dead. They have plugs for your phone all throughout the place. Also, you can open a tab anywhere in the bar and it's good throughout the bar. This is all evidence that this place was designed with the customer in mind!
BBQ pork nachos are great. Quite a few craft beers and friendly staff in a unique building.  Good atmosphere.
Eat, drink, be merry and get rowdy. Really good fries. Just don't take any guff from Danny.

I had an absolutely great time at Exiles. Went there for the first game of the football season and it was very live in there. The food was excellent, prices very reasonable, and the staff was beyond on point. I will recommend all my friends to come here. I'm definitely going back this weekend.
Pretty great. If you're into average looking bartenders that are pretty good at bartending.

Great experience all around. This place is extremely comfortable and found myself there more than once this past weekend. The environment at exiles makes you want to stay awhile and enjoy yourself. I found the staff and the bartenders to be friendly and generally happy people...nice to see for a change. The food is also another reason to go. I was there on Friday night and had some smoked wings and a chicken sandwhich which I highly recommend. I then was back for brunch on Sunday and had the smoked beef hash which was amazing. The chef there knows what she is doing. I will be putting Exiles on my regular list and can't wait to go back soon.
